FBIS3-17718 "drsov060_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Military Publications Merge, To Cease Publication OW2903094094 Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks in Russian 0152 GMT 13 Mar 94 OW2903094094 Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Interview with unidentified captain first rank by unidentified correspondent; place and date not given -- recorded; from the "Aty-Baty" program] [Text] In accordance with the adopted decision, the following armed forces journals will cease publication: VESTNIK PROTIVOVOZDUSHNOY OBORONY [THE AIR DEFENSE HERALD]; VOYENNYY VESTNIK [THE MILITARY HERALD]; AVIATSIYA I KOSMONAVTIKA [AVIATION AND SPACE]; VOYENNO-EKONOMICHESKIY ZHURNAL [THE MILITARY AND ECONOMIC JOURNAL], which until recently was called TYL VOORUZHENNYKH SIL [THE ARMED FORCES REAR]; and TEKHNIKA I VOORUZHENIYE [EQUIPMENT AND ARMS]. From 1 July of this year, we will be publishing the ARMEYSKIY SBORNIK [THE ARMY COLLECTION], which will absorb the topics of and replace the five journals ceasing publication. It has already been included in the subscription catalog, and one will be able to become a subscriber. The three educational and trends journals, ARMIYA [ARMY], SOBESEDNIK VOYNA [THE SOLDIER'S INTERLOCUTOR], and ARGUMENT [ARGUMENT], which were published by the armed forces until recently, will be replaced by a journal called ORIYENTIR [THE ORIENTATOR], the first issue of which we expect will be issued after 1 July.
